With the bisection to edd36a90 it's easy to see the problem:[`urlspec->appURL = (CFURLRef) [NSURL fileURLWithPath: [info->bundle bundlePath]]`](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib/-/commit/edd36a907ba87ffb51ccc447ed7c283dde291c6a#84accd6e468c60d7d54e8c54ce60b55dab8afc66_287_281) allocates the URL in an autorelease pool and [`CFRelease (urlspec->appURL);
`](https://gitlab.gnome.org/GNOME/glib/-/commit/edd36a907ba87ffb51ccc447ed7c283dde291c6a#84accd6e468c60d7d54e8c54ce60b55dab8afc66_300_294) explicitly releases it, but the autorelease pool doesn't know that and when the pthread cleanup timer fires about 10 seconds later the memory location has long since been overwritten with something else by the operating system.

While it's reasonable to just let the thread handle releasing the memory we can make the process more transparent by having our own autorelease pool for `g_osx_app_info_launch_internal`. I've submitted !4448 to do so.

