> Can we add something like:
> 
> ```C
> if (static_resource == next) {
>   return;
> }
> ```

I don’t think that would really help: it would only catch the cases where `static_resource` is registered twice in a row, but not the cases where it’s registered twice with another resource being registered inbetween. When dealing with complicated library initialisers, like `ibus_init()`, I think those cases might happen.

Checking for circularity in the linked list, while also keeping its implementation lock-free, would probably be hard to do. And certainly beyond the scope of “simple things GLib can do to catch bugs in clients”. Because this is a bug in the calling code, not GLib.

Perhaps a simpler and more general fix would be to add the following to the start of the function:
```c
g_return_if_fail (static_resource != NULL);
g_return_if_fail (static_resource->next == NULL);
```

If you want to submit a merge request to do that, that would be great, thanks.

